Egencia LLC Key Developments

Egencia LLC Has Re-Locates Chief Technology Officer, Alex Kaluzny Will to Paris from Seattle
May 30 17
Egencia LLC has announced that chief technology officer, Alex Kaluzny will re-locate to Paris from Seattle. This move is part of the recent Egencia global reorganization as it looks to grow market share globally.


Egencia® Plans to Launch Suite of Expense Management Products for the Modern Business Traveler
Feb 16 17
Egencia® planned to launch a suite of expense management products for the modern business traveler. After revolutionizing the booking experience through technology, Egencia is bringing this innovative spirit to the world of expense management. The Egencia expense management suite will consist of: Egencia Open Sync. Through this new Egencia product, travelers will be able to consolidate receipts and credit card transactions directly in Egencia, and then feed them in one-click into their expense system. This product is currently in beta and will be piloted with a select group of customers and expense partners in the coming weeks. Egencia Open Connect Platform. This platform is based on a powerful set of APIs (application programming interfaces) that feed an ecosystem of Travel and Expense, Traveler Risk Management, and Enterprise Resource Planning partners. Egencia is extending this reporting and data management infrastructure with enhanced functionality; including the ability to extend the platform to new partners. Egencia Integrated Travel and Expense. Egencia will expand its offering to provide a fully integrated travel and expense management solution to create an end-to-end experience that captures booking, fulfilment and expense. Egencia's first fully integrated expense management partner will be its affiliate Traveldoo, withother expense providers to follow.


Egencia Opens Singapore Office
Apr 18 16
Egencia announced an expansion of its already global operation by opening an office in Singapore. With a team of experienced business travel specialists, consultants and account managers, the Singapore office will provide Egencia clients access to local customer service teams with local insight and knowledge. Singapore becomes Egencia's 4th full service point of sale in Asia Pacific offering both Egencia proprietary technology and local service.


